metadata.name: Night royal mansion
metadata.description:
Zhao Huaizhong came out of Zhangtai Palace near noon.



When he returned to his bedchamber, someone wrote down the specific tasks to be arranged for him in a brief book as ordered by King Zhuang Xiang.



Smoke was curling from the copper censer, and the study was filled with the pleasant smell of vegetation.



In the palace of this era, doors and Windows were all designed through the top, almost as high as the room.
